column5: Welcome and I can see you are already fitting in rather well.  Cheers. G
Welcome aboard Dave!
Welcome Dave....GO HABS GO!!!!

Name changed. Pigeontroller.... amazed you can find anyone who can stand you in the boat  Oh you'll fit in here just fine. I understand the Smallie obsession, Musky? Was at a tackle store in London today and was gawking at some of those Musky baits. You guys must have some pretty large for arms pitching those bulldog things with a 2X2 rod. Wow. I'm impressed.
Welcome  Dave
Welcome aboard Dave nice to have you with us.

Hello OFC'ers. My name is Dave and I am new to the board. I have been an avid muskie fisherman for a very long time and more recently a smallmouth bass fanatic as well. Looking forward to adding some intellectual input to the Leafs thread  as well as some fishing stuff too  this is a great forum and looking forward to having some fun! Cheers
Welcome aboard Dave glad to have another musky nut in the crew
My name is Dave  Looking forward to adding some intellectual input to the Leafs thread  Oh gawd, another one    Welcome, and sorry to hear about your laffs (not really)
Welcome aboard Dave.You'll have fun here for sure!!!!!!!
Oh gawd, another one    Welcome, and sorry to hear about your laffs (not really) I wondered how long it would take Matt lol
Welcome Dave!
Welcome aboard....looking forward to your fishing input.

Welcome.  Ya what he said,
Welcome Dave, if you ever want to get out fishing let me know, currently by fishing pardner is a bit of a dork and I could use a new one!

Name changed. Pigeontroller.... amazed you can find anyone who can stand you in the boat
Welcome Dave.   Anxious to see some musky pics.
Well hi Dave you did say the magic words "smallmouth fanatic"  welcome aboard grab a coffee and jump right in !!!! Where abouts are you ? And where do you mostly fish !!!! Cheers

Well hi Dave you did say the magic words "smallmouth fanatic" welcome aboard grab a coffee and jump right in !!!! Where abouts are you ? And where do you mostly fish !!!! Cheers I live in Stoney Creek. My smallie fishing has taken place on the upper and lower Niagara as well as Lake Erie. I fish both Canadian and U.S. waters. While muskie has been my fish of choice for 18 years, the smallmouth fishery that exists in the Niagara region is fantastic!! Favorite way to catch both species is on top. Cheers
Welcome Dave we hope your stay is pleasurable.   Art
Welcome Dave!
Welcome indeed! And you are correct, the smallmouth fishing in Erie is a bass fishing nuts dream! I won't be spoiling your fun though. Steelhead is my vice.
Welcome, i am also muskie and smallie fanatic! Looking gorward to some pics/stories.
Welcome my friend
Musky and smallies...well you have to start somewhere  Welcome to the club. The mods are sleeping between 7pm and 7am, so make sure you edit your posts by around 6am.
Welcome Sir!!!You will enjoy.!
Welcome aboard! I too enjoy slammin' some smallies. Great fun on ultra-light gear
Welcome!!!  Interested in hearing about fishing the Niagra fishery...

Welcome to the site! I'm relatively new compared to some here... but have just started into muskie and if you ever need some company out in the niagara that's going to be my first and most often spot to hit as I'm from Hamilton!
